Add tests for rumpel merge --signoff

`rumpel merge <pod> --signoff` passes --signoff straight through to
git merge.  git only writes the Signed-off-by footer into a commit it
actually creates, so the footer lands on the merge commit whenever one
is produced: the description-file path already forces --no-ff, and the
no-description path needs an explicit --no-ff.  A fast-forward signs
nothing, matching git's own behavior.

Add integration tests covering the sign-off footer in both the
description-on and description-off cases.  No functional change to
rumpel.
